    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden</name>
                    <date when="1888-10-21">Sunday PM</date>
                    <date when="1888-10-21">Oct: 21 '88<ptr target="loc.07527_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute/>
            </opener>

            <p>Again "the same subject continued"&#8212;decidedly cold to-day&#8212;a good fire
                needed&#8212;I ate a good breakfast of stew'd chicken, brown bread, a roast apple
                &#38; chocolate ab't 10&#8212;am writing &#38; reading a little&#8212;friendly
                notices of Nov: B.<ptr target="n3999"/> in Bost: <hi rend="italic"
                    >Transcript</hi> (by Kennedy)<ptr target="n3039"/>&#8212;&#38; in to-day's
                Phila: <hi rend="italic">Press</hi> (I don't know who)<ptr target="loc.07527_n2"
                />&#8212;Probably you have got them sent you&#8212;if not say when you write &#38; I
                will send&#8212;a friendly two or three sticks' full in N Y Herald three weeks
                    ago<ptr target="loc.07527_n3"/>&#8212;did you get it? mostly ab't E Hicks<ptr
                        target="loc.07527_n5"/>&#8212;I suppose you got Mary Costelloe's<ptr
                    target="loc.02189_n1"/> letter to me, I had forwarded you&#8212;</p>

            <p>No Ostler<ptr target="loc.07528_n2"/> now over a week (is that a good sign of his
                verdict on me?)&#8212;bowel movements fair&#8212;no hitch in the progress of the big
                book,<ptr target="n4151"/> but slow&#8212;my dull indomitable inertia of body &#38; brain tyrannic as
                ever&#8212;This enc: f'm <hi rend="italic">Critic</hi> just rec'd&#8212;I have
                ans'd&#8212;sh[or]t letter may appear in next C<ptr target="loc.07527_n4"
                />&#8212;</p>

            <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
        </body>
    </text>
